<topic id="how-to-marklogic">
  <title>Configuring a MarkLogic Database Connection</title>
  <body>
    <p id="p_fnx_cgk_54b">Note that this feature is available in <ph keyref="product"/> Enterprise edition only.</p>
    <p id="p_gnx_cgk_54b">Follow this procedure to configure the support for a MarkLogic database connection:<ol id="ol_hnx_cgk_54b">
        <li id="li_inx_cgk_54b"><ph id="download-marklogic-driver">Download the MarkLogic driver from <xref
              keyref="url_MLCommunity">MarkLogic Community site</xref>.</ph></li>
        <li id="li_jnx_cgk_54b"><xref href="configure-marklogic-datasource.dita#configure-marklogic-datasource"
            >Configure MarkLogic <term>Data Source</term> drivers</xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_knx_cgk_54b"><xref href="configure-marklogic-connection.dita#configure-marklogic-connection"
            >Configure a MarkLogic <term>Connection</term></xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_lnx_cgk_54b">To view your connection, go to the <xref
            href="../topics/relational-database-explorer.dita#relational-database-explorer"
              ><uicontrol>Data Source Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref>
          <ph conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/reopen-view-parenthesis"/> or switch to the
            <uicontrol>Database</uicontrol>
          <xref keyref="glossentry_perspective"><term>perspective</term></xref>.</li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
